To the extent that it is possible to glean meaning from the application, Mr Tsekouras makes the following claims: (1) a claim, akin to an annulment, that he should not have been made a bankrupt;
(2) a claim that Mr Olsen made payments from the bankrupt estate which he should not have made; and
(3)&(4) a claim for compensation.

An application for such an order needs to show that the person against whom such an order is sought:

- habitually and persistently;

- and without any reasonable cause;

- institutes;

- a vexatious proceeding;

- in the Court [or any other Australian court].
